rows: The camera is connected to a TV: Pictures will be displayed on the TV instead of in the camera monitor (üìñ 57).
**Both the TV and camera monitor are blank.**
The display mode selected with the **VIEW MODE** button is **EVF ONLY + üëÅÔ∏è SENSOR**: Put your eye to the viewfinder. Use the **VIEW MODE** button to choose another display mode (üìñ 16).

- The camera is not properly connected: Connect the camera properly (üìñ 57).
- Input on the television is set to ‚ÄúTV‚Äù: Set input to ‚ÄúHDMI‚Äù (üìñ 57).
- The volume on the TV is too low: Use the controls on the television to adjust the volume (üìñ 57).
**The computer does not recognize the camera.**
Be sure the camera and computer are correctly connected (üìñ 255).
**FUJIFILM X RAW STUDIO or FUJIFILM X Acquire fails to correctly detect the camera.**
Check the option selected for **CONNECTION MODE** on the camera. Select **USB RAW CONV./BACKUP RESTORE** before connecting the USB cable (üìñ 263).
